"meanings":["Turkish: ornamental name, nickname, or relationship name from <i>ata</i> ‘father, elder’.","Muslim (mainly Egypt): from a personal name based on Arabic <i>ʿaṭā</i> ‘gift’ (understood as ‘gift from God’). Compare   Atallah   and   Atta  ."]}]},{"name":"ESHE","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Gerd.  Scandinavian Sven.","German:","variant of   Esch  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Esch","meanings":["German:","habitational name from any of several places called Esch, from Old High German <i>asc</i> ‘ash’, or a topographic name for someone who lived near a prominent ash tree.","from Middle High German <i>ezzisch</i> ‘communally owned seeded field’, hence a topographic name for someone who lived by an area where grain was grown or perhaps a status name for someone who owned such land."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Atte ESHE was born about 1248, in Colkirk, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. He married Mrs Atte Eshe about 1273. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"Abt 1248–":"umbes 1248–Surnud","1252–Female":"1252–Surnud","1268–1308":"1268–1308","1248–Male":"1248–Surnud","Abt 1273":"umbes 1273","1248":"1248","1268":"1268","Abt 1248":"umbes 1248","1252":"1252","1308":"1308","Of Colkirk,Norfolk,England":"Colkirk, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Mitford, Norfolk, England":"Mitford, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1248–":"noin 1248–Kuollut","1252–Female":"1252–Kuollut","1268–1308":"1268–1308","1248–Male":"1248–Kuollut","Abt 1273":"noin 1273","1248":"1248","1268":"1268","Abt 1248":"noin 1248","1252":"1252","1308":"1308","Of Colkirk,Norfolk,England":"Colkirk, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Mitford, Norfolk, England":"Mitford, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1248–":"environ 1248–Décédé","1252–Female":"1252–Décédée","1268–1308":"1268–1308","1248–Male":"1248–Décédé","Abt 1273":"environ 1273","1248":"1248","1268":"1268","Abt 1248":"environ 1248","1252":"1252","1308":"1308","Of Colkirk,Norfolk,England":"Colkirk, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Mitford, Norfolk, England":"Mitford, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert Atte ESHE est né environ 1248, à Colkirk, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a épousé Mrs Atte Eshe environ 1273. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"Abt 1248–":"um 1248–Verstorben","1252–Female":"1252–Verstorben","1268–1308":"1268–1308","1248–Male":"1248–Verstorben","Abt 1273":"um 1273","1248":"1248","1268":"1268","Abt 1248":"um 1248","1252":"1252","1308":"1308","Of Colkirk,Norfolk,England":"Colkirk, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Mitford, Norfolk, England":"Mitford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Robert Atte ESHE wurde um 1248 in Colkirk, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hat um 1273 Mrs Atte Eshe geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"Abt 1248–":"about 1248–Desede","1252–Female":"1252–D